    "sections": {
        "description": "<p><strong><a href=\"http://demo.wpzoom.com/foodica/shortcodes\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">View Shortcodes Demo</a></strong><br />\n<strong><a href=\"http://demo.wpzoom.com/originmag/2015/08/07/brabus-bullit-c-class-coupe/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">View Slideshow Shortcode Demo</a></strong></p>\n<p>A suite of useful shortcodes compatible with any existing themes, not just with WPZOOM themes.</p>\n<h3>Shortcodes list</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Slideshow</strong></li>\n<li>Columns</li>\n<li>Buttons</li>\n<li>Tabs</li>\n<li>Icons</li>\n<li>Lists with Icons</li>\n<li>Info Boxes</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Documentation</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.wpzoom.com/docs/how-to-use-built-in-shortcodes/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Read Documentation</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.wpzoom.com/tutorial/how-to-use-the-wpzoom-slideshow-shortcode/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Slideshow Shortcode Documentation</a></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Did you find this plugin helpful? Please consider <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/support/view/wpzoom-shortcodes\" rel=\"ugc\">leaving a 5-star review</a>.</p>\n</blockquote>\n",
        "installation": "<p>Simply search for the plugin name via the <strong>Plugins -&gt; Add New</strong> dialog and click install, or download and extract the plugin, and copy the plugin folder into your wp-content/plugins directory and activate.</p>\n<p>After installation you can add shortcodes by clicking on the new icons appearing in the Classic Editor (Visual Mode): most of the shortcodes are added by clicking the &#8220;W&#8221; icon in the editor, while the Slideshow Shortcode can be added by clicking on the small icon with a landscape.<br />\nShortcodes work also in Gutenberg, and are available only in the Classic Editor block.</p>\n",
        "faq": "\n<dt id='i%20just%20installed%20the%20plugin%20and%20can%27t%20find%20how%20to%20add%20the%20shortcodes%3F'>\nI just installed the plugin and can&#8217;t find how to add the shortcodes?\n</h4>\n<p>\n<p>If you&#8217;re using the Classic Editor, make sure to switch to Visual Editor and you will find icons to add shortcodes.<br />\nIn Gutenberg shortcodes can be added only when using the Classic Editor block.</p>\n</p>\n\n",
        "changelog": "<h4>1.0.5</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Minor bug fixes</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0.4</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Minor bug fixes</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0.3</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Minor bug fixes</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0.2</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fixed input fields sanization</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0.1</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Minor bug fixes</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Initial release.</li>\n</ul>\n"
    },
